The paper deals with a problem related to robot navigation, which is a subfield of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed method is based on Generative Adversarial Networks (GAN), which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of anomaly detection, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the use of the proposed method for robot path planning, which is a subfield of control systems (cs.SY).
